what do you recommend?

Ah, the classic "VS Code on Hyprland" greeting. Since Hyprland is a window manager and not a full-blown desktop environment (like GNOME or KDE), it doesn't come with a "secrets" manager pre-configured. VS Code is looking for a place to store your GitHub tokens and settings sync credentials securely.

To fix this, you need to install a secrets provider and ensure it starts when you log in.

1. Install a Keyring Provider
Most Arch users on Hyprland opt for gnome-keyring. It’s lightweight and handles the "Secret Service" DBus interface that VS Code expects.

Run this in your terminal:

Bash
sudo pacman -S gnome-keyring libsecret
2. Update your Hyprland Config
Installing it isn't enough; the daemon needs to be running. Open your hyprland.conf and add the following line to your exec-once section:

Ini, TOML
exec-once = gnome-keyring-daemon --start --components=secrets
Note: Some users also need to export a variable to tell applications to use the secret service. You can add this to your .zshrc, .bashrc, or a wrapper script:
export PASSWORD_STORE_SET_GPG_OPTS="--keyid-format LONG"

3. The "Force" Method (VS Code Flags)
If the keyring is running but VS Code is still being stubborn, you can force it to use a specific password store via the command line or by editing your .desktop file.

Try launching it once with this flag to see if the error disappears:

Bash
code --password-store="gnome-libsecret"
If that works, you can make it permanent by adding that flag to your ~/.config/code-flags.conf (if you use the Arch package) or by modifying the Exec line in the VS Code desktop entry.

Summary Checklist
Step	Action
Install	gnome-keyring and libsecret
Autostart	Add gnome-keyring-daemon to hyprland.conf
Environment	Ensure dbus is running (usually handled by systemd)
Pro Tip: If you're still getting prompted for a password every time you open VS Code, you might need a Polkit agent (like polkit-kde-agent or sway-polkit) to handle the authentication pop-ups. Most Hyprland setups need one of these to function properly!

